    feat(privacy): add configurable browser fingerprint defense layer
    
    Implements a robust fingerprint defense layer for browser privacy.
    This feature randomizes or spoofs canvas, WebGL, AudioContext,
    user agent, fonts, referer header, timezone, and screen metrics,
    using a session-seeded PRNG for consistent per-session randomization.
    
    - Adds src/lib/privacy/fingerprint.ts with granular, configurable mitigations
    - Exposes toggles in security/privacy settings UI (Profile > Settings)
    - Initializes defenses before React render for maximum protection
    - Updates global store with persistent user-controlled toggles
    - Includes unit tests for randomization, determinism, and toggle logic
    
    Noteworthy: Strong privacy defaults; individual controls allow
    users to restore compatibility or accessibility if needed.

